<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES throughout with Carson remarks during taping of show.
No pickup.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By JOHN ANTCZAK</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BURBANK, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Johnny </PERSON> <PERSON> Carson </PERSON> returned to television Wednesday despite a writers strike, giving a monologue of his own making in which he wisecracked that astrology in the White House finally explains `` the loony tunes things that have been coming out of <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>.'' `` The Tonight Show'' had been in reruns since shortly after the <ORGANIZATION> Writers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guild </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION> struck the film and TV industry March 7. <PERSON> Carson </PERSON> announced last week that reruns of the show would end and he would return to the air, writing his own monologues. <PERSON> Carson </PERSON>, who is not a member of the guild, said at that time possibilities of reaching an agreement with striking writers had been exhausted. On Wednesday, he said the real reason for coming back stemmed from the brouhaha over revelations about the influence of astrology in the White House. `` I just could not stay away any longer from all things that are going on in the country. I was compelled to come back,'' <PERSON> Carson </PERSON> said. `` I'm a Scorpio on the cusp. ... You know, we finally have a clue now as to what the hell -LRB- are -RRB- the loony tunes things that have been coming out of <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>.'' <PERSON> Carson </PERSON> referred to revelations by former White House chief of staff <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> Regan </PERSON> that first lady <PERSON> Nancy </PERSON> <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> regularly consulted an astrologer to determine the timing of President <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON>'s movements <PERSON> Carson </PERSON> said he had not been aware there was a new Cabinet position, Secretary of Health, Education and Soothsaying. He also made brief mention of the strike in both a sincere and joking tone. `` We're glad to be back. As far as the writers strike we're not going to discuss it,'' he said. `` I have a lot of friends who are writers. We hope they join us soon. It is not fun to come to work when you see your friends who you've known for many years standing out on a picket line. Then he quipped, `` And it's a weird picket line. The writers are out there holding up these signs and there's nothing on them.'' <PERSON> Carson </PERSON> explained to out-of-towners that there had been excitement in <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> because of persistent rumors that Nostradamus, a 16th century astrologer, forecast an earthquake for a city widely believed to be <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>. `` He was a flim-flam man of the 16th century,'' <PERSON> Carson </PERSON> observed. `` If Nostradamus were alive today he would be <PERSON> Geraldo </PERSON> <PERSON> Rivera </PERSON>,'' he said, referring to the TV personality who opened <PERSON> Al </PERSON> <PERSON> Capone </PERSON>'s vault to great hype but found next to nothing. <PERSON> Carson </PERSON>'s production company, <ORGANIZATION> Carson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tonight </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, was rebuffed in efforts to get either a waiver from the guild or reach an independent agreeement that would permit the writers to return to work.
