<HEAD>Networks Haul Out Original Shows For Sweeps</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JERRY BUCK</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Television Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> won back first place in the <ORGANIZATION> A.C. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nielsen </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> television ratings from <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> and became the first network in more than seven years to claim the nine top shows. Because of the May sweeps, <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> broadcast mostly original programs for the week that ended Sunday. They face summer reruns and a drought imposed by the scriptwriters' strike. <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> finished more than four ratings points ahead of <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> in gaining its 28th victory in 33 weeks. <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> won the previous week largely on the strength of the final episode of `` Magnum, P.I.'' <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> also won the top nine places, the first time a network has done that since <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> for the week of Nov. 3, 1980. `` Cheers'' took first place. The only non-NBC show to make the top 10 was <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Who's the Boss?'' Besides regular series, the <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> movie `` The Taking of Flight 847: The <PERSON> Uli </PERSON> <PERSON> Derickson </PERSON> Story'' was seventh and the first half of the miniseries `` Something Is Out There'' was ninth. <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` The Bourne Identity'' was in 11th place with its opening chapter. It teamed up with the <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> Sunday show `` Something Is Out There'' to send the <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> drama `` The Caine Mutiny Court-Martial'' to 58th place. <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s average rating for the week was 15.6; <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION>' was 11.5 and <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> 11.2. The rating is a percentage of the nation's estimated 88.6 million households with television