<HEAD>Customs Dispute Resolved Ending Delays At Italian Border Points</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Government and union negotiators settled a labor dispute involving customs officials that had backed up freight at border points. The settlement was reached Tuesday by Finance Minister <PERSON> Emilio </PERSON> <PERSON> Colombo </PERSON> and union leaders. <LOCATION> Colombo </LOCATION> said <LOCATION> Italy </LOCATION>'s customs administration will be reformed to grant customs officers a pay raise and to redefine their duties. Thousands of trucks were backed up at the crossing points with <LOCATION> Switzerland </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Austria </LOCATION> last week after Italian officers refused to work overtime to clear customs documents. An official at the Italian-Swiss border point of <LOCATION> Chiasso </LOCATION> said the situation was back to normal after the settlement was announced.
