<HEAD>Four People Found Slain In Italian Villa</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN ANDREA IN BASANICO, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Four people were found shot to death in a ransacked villa near the <LOCATION> Adriatic </LOCATION> beach resort of <LOCATION> Rimini </LOCATION>, police said. The victims, whose hands and feet were bound, were killed with a shot through the head, police said. They were identified as <PERSON> Luigi </PERSON> <PERSON> Pagliarani </PERSON>, 60, and his wife, <PERSON> Patricia </PERSON> <PERSON> Schfield </PERSON>, 58, and <PERSON> Sergio </PERSON> <PERSON> Galassi </PERSON>, 66, and his wife <PERSON> Silvana </PERSON> <PERSON> di </PERSON> <PERSON> Vita </PERSON>, 59. Police in the nearby town of <LOCATION> Riccione </LOCATION> said a relative of <LOCATION> Pagliarani </LOCATION> discovered the bodies Tuesday in the living room of the small villa. The safe was empty and the house had been ransacked, police said, adding that it appeared the couples were victims of a robbery.
