 Actor <PERSON> Henry </PERSON> <PERSON> Winkler </PERSON> told 120 outstanding <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> students that they can fulfill their dreams even if the obstacles seem insurmountable. `` I was n't very good in school,'' admitted <PERSON> Winkler </PERSON>, who gained fame as the character `` Fonzie'' on television's `` Happy Days.'' `` I have dyslexia,'' <PERSON> Winkler </PERSON> said referring to a learning disorder that impairs reading ability. `` I was told that I was never going to be able to live out my dream.'' Instead, <PERSON> Winkler </PERSON> went on to graduate from college, and earned a master's degree in drama at <ORGANIZATION> Yale </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION>. The rest is TV history. `` I dreamed of doing what I do now,'' said <PERSON> Winkler </PERSON>, who works primarily as a producer of the TV series `` MacGyver.'' <PERSON> Winkler </PERSON> was among the hosts Tuesday at the <ORGANIZATION> Los </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Angeles </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Unified </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> School </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> District </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Youth Recognition Day'' for outstanding students ranging from fifth to 12th grade.
