<HEAD>Another Yacht Seized As Ark Royal Leaves Key West</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KEY WEST, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> authorities released one luxury yacht seized under the `` zero tolerance'' anti-drug policy, but announced the seizure of a similar vessel also found with minuscule amounts of drugs on board. The 133-foot Ark Royal was released Tuesday afternoon after <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Rogerson </PERSON>, president of the <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> company that owns the vessel, paid $ 1,600 in fines and fees and agreed not to hold the government responsible. The Ms. <PERSON> Mindy </PERSON>, a $ 600,000, 52-foot sportfishing boat owned by the Cigarette Racing Team of <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Miami </LOCATION>, was seized Monday as it returned from the <LOCATION> Bahamas </LOCATION> and docked in <LOCATION> Port </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Salerno </LOCATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> announced Tuesday. <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Customs </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> agents turned up cocaine residue on a dollar bill and traces of marijuana in a plastic bag, according to the <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION>. Neither person aboard the Ms. <PERSON> Mindy </PERSON> _ ship's captain <PERSON> Lewis </PERSON> <PERSON> Shaver </PERSON> and an unidentified first mate _ was charged with drug possession. Also seized under the policy last week was a 68-foot shrimper. Officials have not decided whether to pursue civil forfeiture of the boat or allow a fine to paid as in the case of the <ORGANIZATION> Ark </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Royal </ORGANIZATION>, said <PERSON> Leon </PERSON> <PERSON> Guinn </PERSON>, assistant regional Customs supervisor. <PERSON> Rogerson </PERSON>, president of the <ORGANIZATION> Tomima </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> and chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> Rogerson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Aircraft </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGA