<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>SAN ANTONIO, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Police have arrested a former congressional candidate on charges that he tried to hire a hit man to kill Mayor <PERSON> Henry </PERSON> <PERSON> Cisneros </PERSON> for $ 5,000, officials said today. Officials arrested <PERSON> Parker </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> Abell </PERSON> on Tuesday and charged him with solicitation of capital murder, said District Attorney <PERSON> Fred </PERSON> <PERSON> Rodriguez </PERSON>. `` He was doing it to make a statement. He wanted to get publicity,'' <PERSON> Rodriguez </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Rodriguez </PERSON> said <PERSON> Abell </PERSON> had mentioned other possible targets, including State Comptroller <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Bullock </PERSON>, but decided on <PERSON> Cisneros </PERSON>. `` <PERSON> Bullock </PERSON>'s name was mentioned, ... but for whatever reasons, whether it was that -LRB- <PERSON> Bullock </PERSON> -RRB- was out of town or not a big enough name, he settled on Mayor <PERSON> Henry </PERSON> <PERSON> Cisneros </PERSON>. He wanted someone at the local level, but with a national reputation,'' <PERSON> Rodriguez </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Rodriguez </PERSON> said he informed the mayor's office of the alleged plot, but did not recommend more protection for the mayor. <PERSON> Abell </PERSON> sought the 23rd Congressional District seat in 1982 as a Liberterian and told detectives he was now leader of a political extremists' group, the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Patriots </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Gary </PERSON> <PERSON> Johnson </PERSON>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> secretary of <ORGANIZATION> Libertarian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION>, said today that <PERSON> Abell </PERSON> is no longer a dues-paying member and is not on the party mailing list. <PERSON> Rodriguez </PERSON> said the state's investigation began about a month ago after <ORGANIZATION> Internal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Revenue </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANI