<HEAD>5-Year-Old Credited With Friend's Rescue</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHILLICOTHE, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A 5-year-old boy who was injured after pushing his friend from the path of a car said Wednesday he feels like a hero. `` He said he had to do what he had to do,'' <PERSON> Sandy </PERSON> <PERSON> Bloomfield </PERSON> said. `` But I do n't want him to be a hero all the time.'' Her son, <PERSON> Ronald </PERSON> <PERSON> Whitaker </PERSON>, was hurt Sunday when he grabbed 5-year-old <PERSON> Bobby </PERSON> <PERSON> Crink </PERSON>'s shirt and pushed him out of the way of a car. `` The car was coming as he was running out in the street,'' <PERSON> Ronald </PERSON> said. `` I had to push him out of the way.'' <PERSON> Ronald </PERSON> was hit in the leg by the car. He was treated at a hospital for bumps and bruises. `` I was standing on the corner and I saw <PERSON> Ron </PERSON> hesitate and I knew what he was trying to do,'' Mrs. <PERSON> Bloomfield </PERSON> said. Police said the driver hit her car's brakes and turned to try to avoid the boys.
