 <PERSON> Ayatollah </PERSON> <PERSON> Ruhollah </PERSON> <PERSON> Khomeini </PERSON> appointed a little-known army officer as <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>'s armed forces chief of staff. Brig. Gen. <PERSON> Ali </PERSON> <PERSON> Shahbazi </PERSON> was sworn in Monday, three weeks after <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION> recaptured the <LOCATION> Faw </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Peninsula </LOCATION> in a surprise assault. Western analysts believe the appointment stems from the Faw loss and defeats in the <LOCATION> Persian </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Gulf </LOCATION> at the hands of the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, signaling a shift in <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>'s strategy in the 7 -LCB- - year-old Iran-Iraq war
