<HEAD>Two Baby Rattles, One Puzzle Game Recalled Over Choking Hazard</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The Consumer Product <ORGANIZATION> Safety </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> announced Wednesday the recall of two brands of baby rattles and a puzzle game because they present a choking hazard to infants. The commission said <ORGANIZATION> Li </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Peng </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Enterprises </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> withdrew its <ORGANIZATION> Rainbow </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bell </ORGANIZATION> rattle, and Toys-R-Us of <LOCATION> Rochelle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Park </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.J. </LOCATION>, withdrew its Crib Pals Shake and Twist Baby Rattle and its Colorforms Story Book Puzzle. The Rainbow rattles, item CT-8013, are plastic with a handle made of what appears to be beads at one end and four bell-shaped noise makers in a circle at the other end. The commission said it did not know of any injuries caused by the rattles, but said they posed a choking hazard because the handle is small enough to enter a child's mouth and can reach the back of the throat. About 86,400 were sold between June 1987 and August 1987 for $ 2.85. The Crib Pals Shake and Twist Baby Rattles, No. 098132, are 5 -LCB- inches by 1 -RCB- inches and have a ball containing liquid and six colored pellets. The commission said the rattle can break during use and the pieces present a potential choking hazard, although no injuries or deaths have been reported. Approximately 24,000 were sold from March 1986 to December 1987 through Toys-R-Us stores for $ 1.48. The Colorforms No. 150 Story Book Puzzles have five wooden pieces and come in two models, the Pinky Brite Bear and the Rosy Brite Bear. Some pieces are small enough to present a choking hazard, the commission said, although no injuries had been reported. About 12,000 puzzles were sold from September 1986 to December 1987 through Toys-R-Us for $ 5.97.
