<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Pat </PERSON> <PERSON> Robertson </PERSON> announced Wednesday that he would halt his Republican presidential race next week, and said in a newspaper inerview that he will likely return to his financially ailing <ORGANIZATION> Christian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Broadcasting </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Network </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Barbara </PERSON> <PERSON> Gattullo </PERSON>, a spokeswoman for Americans for <PERSON> Robertson </PERSON>, said the decision to return to <ORGANIZATION> CBN </ORGANIZATION> is `` not set in stone, but the important thing is whether or not he returns to <ORGANIZATION> CBN </ORGANIZATION>, he will continue to be involved in politics.'' She said <PERSON> Robertson </PERSON> would file papers shortly with the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Election </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> for a new political action committee _ Americans for the Republic. <PERSON> Robertson </PERSON> himself, speaking to reporters outside the White House, endorsed Vice President <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>, who already had the <ORGANIZATION> GOP </ORGANIZATION> nomination well in hand. The former television evangelist said he would formally withdraw from the race Monday. `` I will be making that official on Monday, as a candidate, because the race now is over and the people that I wanted to bring through the process are pretty much home now in relation to their races,'' he responded when asked if he were withdrawing. But an aide, <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Pinsky </PERSON>, later described <PERSON> Robertson </PERSON>'s planned move as a suspension, rather than a withdrawal. Asked whether he would be releasing his delegates, <PERSON> Robertson </PERSON> responded: `` Well, of course, I will be releasing them.'' `` Many of them were not really bound to me because in the caucuses, it has to do with their own preferences. However, the procedures go on the first ballot, 