<DATELINE>AMRITSAR, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Security forces and <ORGANIZATION> Sikh </ORGANIZATION> militants ceased fire Wednesday as negotiations began to end the three-day siege of <LOCATION> Sikhism </LOCATION>'s holiest shrine, police and witnesses said. Up to 12 people were killed during the siege that started Monday after Sikh militants began firing from the Golden Temple complex at police posts on nearby rooftops. Elsewhere in <LOCATION> Punjab </LOCATION> state, five people were killed in attacks late Tuesday night and early Wednesday, the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> India </ORGANIZATION> reported. The head Sikh priest, <PERSON> Jasbir </PERSON> <PERSON> Singh </PERSON> <PERSON> Rode </PERSON>, held inconclusive talks with senior police officials late Wednesday as 2,500 paramilitary troops around the 400-year-old temple and an estimated 100 Sikh militants inside stopped firing. `` We have many options,'' Punjab Gov. <PERSON> S.S. </PERSON> <PERSON> Ray </PERSON> told a news conference, referring to the talks. He did not elaborate. Militant Sikhs have been waging a guerrilla war for an independent homeland since 1982. Although a majority in <LOCATION> Punjab </LOCATION>, Sikhs comprise only 2 percent of <LOCATION> India </LOCATION>'s total population of 800 million people. The Sikhs claim they are discriminated against by <PERSON> Hindus </PERSON>, who make up 82 percent of the nationwide population. An <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> correspondent allowed inside the shrine saw the decomposing bodies of three men and one woman. Sikh militants said the four were shot by security men firing from rooftops. Militants holding automatic weapons huddled behind marble pillars and vowed to carry on their resistance. `` We will continue to die but we shall never be destroyed,'' said Sikh militant <PERSON> Nirvair </PERSON> <PERSON> Singh </PERSON>. Young Sikhs, most yet to sprout a beard, were seen carrying automatic weapons and chanting `` Sikhs will rule!'' Earlier plans to lift a curfew in most of <LOCATION> Amritsar </LOCATION>'s old walled city failed, police officer <PERSON> Singh </PERSON> said. The curfew was ordered Monday when Sikh extremists began firing from the temple complex at rooftop police posts. <PERSON> A.A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Siddiqui </PERSON>, deputy inspector general of police, said at least 10 people have died and 10 have been injured since violence began Monday. But Sikh militants inside the shrine said at least 12 people have died. Three people were killed early Wednesday in a heavy exchange of fire between extremists in the temple complex and security forces. In <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Delhi </LOCATION>, <PERSON> P. </PERSON> <PERSON> Chidambaram </PERSON>, minister of state for home affairs, told <ORGANIZATION> Parliament </ORGANIZATION> Wednesday `` other forces'' were being moved to <LOCATION> Amritsar </LOCATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> India </ORGANIZATION> reported. He did not elaborate. The Home Ministry is responsible for internal security. The army was sent into the Golden Temple complex in June 1984 to drive Sikh extremists from the shrine. Later that year, Prime Minister <PERSON> Indira </PERSON> <PERSON> Gandhi </PERSON> was assassinated by two of her Sikh bodyguards in revenge. Reports said Wednesday that police cut off electricity and water to the temple. <LOCATION> Amritsar </LOCATION> city officials said lines were down but said militants had cut them. Government spokesman J.F. <PERSON> Brar </PERSON> said extremists cut electrical lines Tuesday night to make sure no lights inside the shrine would illuminate their positions. He said this also cut the water supply, as electricity is needed to operate the system's pumps. More than 800 pilgrims were evacuated from the complex Tuesday to keep them out of the crossfire. The complex covers an area equivalent to more than five city blocks. The temple is located in the center of a pool.
