<HEAD>LTV Announces Sale Of Warren Works</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: updates with company announcement</NOTE>
<DATELINE>WARREN, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> LTV </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Steel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> today said it has signed a contract to sell its steel plant in <LOCATION> Warren </LOCATION> to the <ORGANIZATION> Renco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>. Terms of the sale were not disclosed in the company's announcement Included in the sale is <ORGANIZATION> LTV </ORGANIZATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Republic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Drainage </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Products </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Canton </LOCATION> and its six plants, the company said. The Cleveland-based <ORGANIZATION> LTV </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Steel </ORGANIZATION> said completion of the sale is targeted for June 30 and is subject to the approval of <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bankruptcy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, which has jurisdiction over <ORGANIZATION> LTV </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>'s reorganization proceedings. In 1986, the Dallas-based <ORGANIZATION> LTV </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, parent company of <ORGANIZATION> LTV </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Steel </ORGANIZATION>, filed for reorganization under Chapter 11 of the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Bankruptcy Code. <ORGANIZATION> LTV </ORGANIZATION> announced last November that it wanted to sell or find a business partner for its Warren plant, which is the largest steel mill remaining in the <LOCATION> Mahoning </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Valley </LOCATION>. The plant has about 2,200 employees. <ORGANIZATION> LTV </ORGANIZATION> described the <ORGANIZATION> Renco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> as a privately held concern with 15 diversified manufacturing and distribution operations nationwide. All employees at the Warren plant and the Republic Drainage plants, including management, are expected to be retained, <ORGANIZATION> LTV </ORGANIZATION> said. <ORGANIZATION> LTV </ORGANIZATION>'s coke plant in <LOCATION> Warren </LOCATION> is not included in the sale and will continue to be part of <ORGANIZATION> LTV </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Steel </ORGANIZATION>, the company said. <ORGANIZATION> LTV </ORGANIZATION> President <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> H. </PERSON> <PERSON> Hoag </PERSON> said repairs to the <PERSON> Warren </PERSON> blast furnace will be completed as scheduled later this summer. `` We believe this sale of the <PERSON> Warren </PERSON> <PERSON> Works </PERSON> and the drainage products plants is in the best interest of <ORGANIZATION> LTV </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Steel </ORGANIZATION>, the affected employees and local communities. We urge the employees, their unions and the communities of the <LOCATION> Mahoning </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Valley </LOCATION> to extend their welcome and cooperation to <ORGANIZATION> Renco </ORGANIZATION> as it becomes a major employer and force in the local economy,'' <PERSON> Hoag </PERSON> said in a statement. <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Rep. <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Traficant </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-Ohio </LOCATION>, said he was informed of the sales this morning by <ORGANIZATION> LTV </ORGANIZATION> officials. <PERSON> Traficant </PERSON> represents the <LOCATION> Mahoning </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Valley </LOCATION> area. `` The good news is that they will retain all management and hourly workers,'' said <PERSON> Traficant </PERSON>. `` The questionable news however is that the group has very limited activity in the steel industry. However, our local people have turned the plant around and made it profitable.'' <PERSON> Hoag </PERSON> said last fall that the sale would fit in with the company's plans to concentrate its operations and capital investment primarily in three flat-rolled facilities in <LOCATION> Cleveland </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ind. </LOCATION>, and <LOCATION> Hennepin </LOCATION>, Ill. The Warren plant has an annual raw steel production capacity of 1.5 million tons, the company said. It produces hot and cold rolled sheet and strip steel, hot-dipped galvanized sheet steel, silicon steel and terne plate. Republic Drainage buys half of the zinc-coated steel shiopped out of the Warren Works. Republic Drainage employs 150 people at plants in <LOCATION> Canton </LOCATION>; <LOCATION> Owego </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.Y. </LOCATION>; <LOCATION> Charlotte </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.C. </LOCATION>; <LOCATION> Harrisburg </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Pa. </LOCATION>; <LOCATION> Bristol </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Tenn. </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Seneca </LOCATION>, S.C.
